<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> rdfs:label "Secondary Source: Broughton MRR II" ;
	a dprr:SecondarySource ;
	dprr:hasName "The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. II" ;
	dprr:hasID 2 ;
	dprr:hasBiblio "Broughton, T. R. S., The Magistrates of the Roman Republic, Vol. II (99 B.C.-31 B.C.). Published by the American Philological Association. New York 1952." ;
	dprr:hasAbbreviation "Broughton MRR II" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/26> rdfs:label "Secondary Source: Suolahti 1955" ;
	a dprr:SecondarySource ;
	dprr:hasName "Suolahti" ;
	dprr:hasID 26 ;
	dprr:hasBiblio "Suolahti, J., The junior officers of the Roman army in the Republican period : a study on social structure. Helsinki : Suomalainen Tiedeakatemia, 1955." ;
	dprr:hasAbbreviation "Suolahti 1955" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6426> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6426" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Octavian in the Illyrian campaign, and met his death near Siscia in a naval battle on the Sava (Dio 49.37.6, without title)." ;
	dprr:hasID 6426 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6424> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6424" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Octavian in the Illyrian campaign, and met his death near Siscia in a naval battle on the Sava (Dio 49.37.6, without title)." ;
	dprr:hasID 6424 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6393> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6393" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 38, and 37, Legates. He did some damage to Octavian's fleet as it advanced from Cumae (Dio 49.1.3), and again deserted from Pompey to Octavian, but received no position of trust (App. BC 5.100-102; Dio 49.1.3-4)." ;
	dprr:hasID 6393 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6359> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6359" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Resenting his position under Calvisius, Menodorus deserted Octavian, returned to Sextus Pompey with seven (or six) vessels, and became one of his officers again (see Promagistrates, on Calvisius; and 36, Legates)." ;
	dprr:hasID 6359 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6343> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6343" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A freedman of Pompey the Great, and an important officer, Legate or Prefect, in the fleet of Sextus Pompey, for whom he held Sardinia (see 40, and 39, Legates). He deserted to Octavian, bringing him Sardinia, a fleet of sixty ships, and three legions (App. BC 5.78-80; Dio 48.45; Oros. 6.18.21; Zonar. 10.23; cf. Suet. Aug. 74.1), and was rewarded by promotion to the equestrian order (Suet.; App. BC; Dio; Zonar.). He was with Calvisius in the battle off Cumae, and used his experience to aid in reducing losses in the storm at the Sicilian straits (App. BC 5.81-84, and 89; Dio 48.48.1-2; Oros. 6.18.21; Zonar. 10.23). He pursued Apollophanes (see above) when Sextus Pompey sent him to Africa (Dio 48.48.6)." ;
	dprr:hasID 6343 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6313> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6313" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A commander, Legate or Prefect, in the fleet of Sextus Pompey, and governor of Sardinia and Corsica (App. BC 5.78). He urged Pompey not to make the treaty of Misenum (App. BC 5.70, cf. 71, and 77); and at the celebration of the peace when Antony and Octavian were present on Pompey’s ship Menodorus proposed to sail away with them as prisoners but Pompey forbade it (Plut. Ant. 32.3-5; App. BC 5.73; Dio 48.38.2). See 39, Legates." ;
	dprr:hasID 6313 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6289> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6289" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See above, on Menecrates; and Promagistrates, on Lurius. Both were probably prominent Pompeian officers from 43 B. C. on." ;
	dprr:hasID 6289 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10309> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10309" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/26> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "C.179, 184, 190, 191, 197, 200 (MRR lists as legatus but admits praefectus as possible, Suolahti has praefectus classis)." ;
	dprr:hasID 10309 .
